ROCKLAND, Maine â€” Rockland police arrested the RSU 13 bus driver on Thursday involved in the crash that killed a 12-year-old student last November.

Jeffrey Colburn, 65, of Camden faces a manslaughter charge, according to a [social media post](https://www.facebook.com/share/p/1C8ShuNUfw/) from Rockland police. A grand jury indicted Colburn, and the Knox County District Attorney's Office issued the arrest warrant.

Authorities identified Colburn as the driver involved in an incident Nov. 21, where 12-year-old [Brayden Callahan was struck by a school bus](/article/news/local/public-safety/rsu-13-student-hit-by-school-bus-rockland-intersection-rockland-maine/97-8f3d5f3d-161b-480c-aad8-71198069f4f8) after getting off. Colburn was reportedly no longer employed by the school district last December.

